nM_n(\\mathbb{F}_2)$ and $k=(k_1,\\ldots,k_n)\\in \\{1,\\ldots,n\\}^n$ chosen\nuniformly at random. It is shown here that $L_1$ is a KS space (with $C=\n2e^2/(e^2-1)$, which is best possible), implying the above nonembeddability\nstatement. Links to the Ribe program are discussed, as well as related open\nproblems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Jan 2015 16:05:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 27 Jan 2015 14:40:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-01-28"}
